{"id": "EUVD-2025-13043", "enisaUuid": "f4e23e5a-55b8-3bb3-9e60-6ebe1074a387", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nksmbd: fix use-after-free in __smb2_lease_break_noti()\n\nMove tcp_transport free to ksmbd_conn_free. If ksmbd connection is\nreferenced when ksmbd server thread terminates, It will not be freed,\nbut conn->tcp_transport is freed. __smb2_lease_break_noti can be performed\nasynchronously when the connection is disconnected. __smb2_lease_break_noti\ncalls ksmbd_conn_write, which can cause use-after-free\nwhen conn->ksmbd_transport is already freed.", "datePublished": "2025-05-01T15:31:44", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-14T18:31:18", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-37777", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/21a4e47578d44c6b37c4fc4aba8ed7cc8dbb13de", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/e59796fc80603bcd8569d4d2e10b213c1918edb4", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/1aec4d14cf81b7b3e7b69eb1cfa94144eed7138e", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/1da8bd9a10ecd718692732294d15fd801c0eabb5"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-37777", "GHSA-4748-h423-7xq4"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "1b1fc884-0f62-3a6d-a18f-8e5fbf3d7fee", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <21a4e47578d44c6b37c4fc4aba8ed7cc8dbb13de"}, {"id": "1e8789a6-6f87-3fae-9341-0a577627259e", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.6.101"}, {"id": "37bffc36-0198-3bcf-83b0-0a3bdbdce9f4", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.15"}, {"id": "49a9b263-bee1-3f77-8355-6863fc99b138", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.14.4"}, {"id": "4ef4edf1-d648-320f-81dd-f50ab7f5eb7c", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "0626e6641f6b467447c81dd7678a69c66f7746cf <1aec4d14cf81b7b3e7b69eb1cfa94144eed7138e"}, {"id": "7c8395b2-0f69-3ece-9cf7-ffdf954071fc", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "pa